A man died in Elysian Park when a hillside collapsed on the tent where he was sleeping.
In Studio City, a man and his children were rescued from a collapsed hillside home.
Storms in Southern California caused floods, mudslides, and power outages, leading to multiple deaths and rescues.
The turbulent weather prompted evacuations and road closures, with over 700 reported accidents.
The relentless rain overwhelmed the region, with some areas receiving record-breaking rainfall.
The devastation included a deadly mudslide in La Conchita and ongoing rescue efforts.
Despite a brief respite, more rain was expected, prolonging the chaos.
